{{Expand Polish|Jeremi Wasiutyński|date=April 2012}}
'''Jeremi Wasiutyński''' (1907–2005) was a [[Poland|Polish]] astronomer and philosopher.

He made a detailed study of the mechanical and thermal effects of turbulence in rotating stars.

His book ''The Solar Mystery'' offered an in-depth re-evaluation of the influences that drove Copernicus to formulate his heliocentric model. 

